<br>
And I learned that we are a rather careless country, quick to condemn, thoughtless of most others except ourselves. What we need is to set an example through the ideals that our country supposedly stands for instead of being the &quot;bully of the world&quot; like I've heard this country called. Because, seeing as how we're one of the most powerful nations, sometimes choosing not to exercise that power is best.. with too much power comes corruption, and exercising power over too many smaller countries gets one the reputation of a bully of sorts. Not that we shouldn't have retaliated, I'm glad we've mostly disbanded the Taliban... However, with a little more care and a little less zealousness we could have avoided killing some innocents in our retaliation.<br>
<br>
